<p class="cgu-intro">
    On JS Brokers, the <strong>token</strong> is the unit measuring your usage of the platform.
    It enables fair, pay-as-you-go pricing while keeping a renewable <strong>free tier</strong>
    to get started and work day to day.
</p>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>1. What is a token?</h2>
    <p>
        A token measures the volume of data exchanged between your browser and our servers.
        Each operation "weighs" a number of tokens, deducted from your balance.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>2. When are tokens consumed?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Output (reading)</strong>: every entity displayed/downloaded to your screen costs <strong>2 tokens</strong>. Loading a list of 20 items therefore costs 20 × 2 = 40 tokens.</li>
        <li><strong>Input (writing)</strong>: every save (creation or update) costs a variable weight depending on the entity type.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>3. Entity weights on write</h2>
    <table class="cgu-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Entity</th><th>Weight (tokens)</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Company</td><td>200</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Endorsement</td><td>100</td></tr>
